'''Alf Boyd''' (22 October 1920 – 3 July 1998) was a Scottish professional [[association football|footballer]] who played as a [[wing half]].

==Career==
Born in [[Dundee]], Boyd played in Scotland for [[Dundee North End F.C.|Dundee North End]], [[St Johnstone F.C.|St Johnstone]] and [[Dundee F.C.|Dundee]]; he was later player-coach of Marist Bros. in South Africa.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.neilbrown.newcastlefans.com/player11/alfboyd.htm|title=Profile|accessdate=27 April 2014|publisher=Post War English & Scottish Football League A - Z Player's Transfer Database}}</ref> He went on to manage [[Durban City F.C.|Durban City]].<ref name=herald/>

